File: Former Steinhoff CEO Markus Jooste tendered his resignation in June, saying the outcome of a proposed disciplinary inquiry has been predetermined. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Institute of Chartered Accountants (SAICA) will institute disciplinary proceedings against former Steinhoff CEO Markus Jooste. The body has rejected his resignation and decided to suspend him instead. Jooste tendered his resignation in June, saying the outcome of a proposed disciplinary inquiry has been predetermined. READ: Markus Jooste blames board for Steinhoff woes SAICA says a resignation can not be used to evade the disciplinary action. The institute says it has told Jooste's lawyers the inquiry will be conducted in an independent, lawful and fair manner.